# ShatterSeek Analysis Pipeline

Detect chromothripsis events from SV and CNV data.

## Input File Format

### SV file (sv.csv)
```
chrom1  start1  chrom2  end2  SVtype  strand1  strand2
chr1    1000    chr1    2000  DEL     +        -
```

### CNV file (cn.csv)
```
chrom   start   end     CN
chr1    1000    2000    3
```

## Usage

### 1. Prepare input files
```bash
sh prepare_input.sh <sample_name> <svaba_anno> <manta_anno> <jabba_seg> <output_dir>
```

### 2. Run ShatterSeek
```bash
Rscript ShatterSeek.R -s sv.csv -c cn.csv -n sample_name -o output_dir
```

### 3. Replot (optional)
```bash
Rscript plot_ShatterSeek.R -r sample.chromothripsis.Rdata -n sample_name -c chr1 -o output_dir --redir result_dir
```

## Output Files

- `sample.chromothripsis.Rdata` - R object file
- `sample.chromSummary.txt` - Chromothripsis event summary
- `chr*.pdf` - Visualization plots per chromosome

## Dependencies

- R packages: ShatterSeek, optparse, gridExtra, cowplot, ggplot2
